href="http://pub69.ezboard.com/bvea " target="_blank"> Vea Victis</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uazndailow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AznDailow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Been around a while</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(2/11/02 12:29:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1746.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re:</span><hr size=1> There's not much difference between a level 59 and a level 60 Paladin. IMO the &quot;key&quot; level for a Paladin is 59 because that's the level they get Celestial Cleansing, and Ressurection. At 60, we become buff whores due to Divine Strength.<br>
<br>
As for Paladins as a class, it really depends on how you want to play one. If you bring a Paladin to a raid, you have to have a certain mentality, or else you'll just be unhappy. Tanking is usually left to Warriors, damage output isn't that great, and most spells are useless. That being said, you won't be the &quot;star player&quot; of the raid, so to speak, but you do contribute to the &quot;little&quot; things - like topping off your group's HP for example. Then again, at 58/59, a Paladin does become an effective backup healer for the group.<br>
<br>
Paladins really shine in groups though. They're tied with SKs as second best tanking class in the game, and very versatile as well. Stuns, heals, some limited crowd control, etc.<br>
<br>
On top of that, there are certain roleplay elements that may make the class fun for you. Personally, I think it's great being able to fight your way down somewhere to help CR someone - the whole &quot;macho dude&quot; saving the day is amusing to say the least.<br>
<br>
To sum it up, I guess if you're a powergamer, you would probably be better off as a full blown cleric or warrior. If you want to play for fun, try it out and see for yourself how you like it. Recommendations won't do you as much good as first hand experience. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=1746.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=1746.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1746.topic&index=5><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/grunge/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=1746.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.threadControl?topicID=1746.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/grunge/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1746.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1746.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub42.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="ayonaerofrm1">General Forum<option value="ayonaerofrm6">NAG (Nearly Anything Goe